formatted_address: Singapore, Hougang St 21, 212号#01-329530 邮政编码: 530212
name: Kovan 212

reviews.text:
(Apologies for not taking down the stall’s name)
Accidentally discovered this stall, selling Malay/Indonesian dishes in a economical rice style.
Tried their ayam penyet, pretty good and authentic.
Chicken is a little dry but overall texture and taste are good. Chilli is not too bad, acceptable.
Recommended.

There is a new stall open recently. They shifted here from Hougang Ave 1. Selling assorted noodles such as, prawn noodles, fishball noodles, lor me, laksa, etc. The portion is generous and served with quite a lot of ingredients. Taste good and not expensive too.

Coffeehouse food are fine. But NOT that grumpy middle aged woman who cleared and cleaned the table.  She is also taking drinks order, but refused to do so, by claiming that she is busy - when she sat there digging her nose?!!!  The Kopitiam boss ought to reprimand such a unhygienic female worker there!

The western cuisine foodcourt waste my time bruh, I ordered my fried rice and specifically said no egg. They give me the fried rice and said that there was no egg inside, I cycled all the way to a place to settle down since cannot dine in, then when I open the packet, there is egg inside, I went back all the way just to hear them said that they cannot cook the fried rice without egg, u cld hv told me earlier rite so I cld order something else
The food was great, is just that the place was too crowded and stuffy when I visit.
